## Pre-flight — read before responding

Before any work in this project, read in order:

1. .claude/instructions.md — Layer 2 runtime law for this project.
2. Most recent file in .claude/sessions/ matching pattern YYYY-MM-DD.md — last daily handoff.
3. BACKLOG.md at project root — current tasks.
4. .claude/inbox/ — list contents. For each item, either route to the right place (sessions, state, knowledge), summarize for Operator review, or ask Operator what to do.
5. PROJECT.md at project root — project facts and configuration.

Then respond to the Operator's first message. If the message is a conversational opener (hi, what's next, продолжим), respond by stating what you read and proposing a first step based on it. Do not start work without this preflight.

